Package game

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ActionFactory
    Interface for behaviour classes to be added to Actor to get actions in return.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddCoinsAction
    Action that transfers the coins in a small pouch to a coin pouch, then causes the empty small pouch to disappear.
    Application
    Driver class which sets up the game map, adds actor to map, then run the game once.
    AttackYugoAction
    Special Action for attacking YugoMaxx.
    BuildRocketAction
    Action that uses a rocket body and a rocket engine on a rocket pad to build a rocket.
    CoinPouch
    A class representing a coin pouch item, it is an inventory item and is associated with coin value that represents the amount of coins it contains.
    Door
    Class representing a locked door of terrain type.
    DrMaybe
    Class representing Doctor Maybe which is an enemy.
    Enemy
    Base class for enemy classes including Grunt, Goon, Ninja and DrMaybe.
    FillPistolAction
    Action that fills a water pistol with water.
    Floor
    Class representing a floor of terrain type.
    FollowBehaviour
    A behaviour that allows Actor to follow another Actor, thus allowing it to perform MoveActorAction to location nearer to the other Actor if any.
    GameManagement
    Manages the game by setting up different requirements and settings of the game.
    GameWorld
    Class representing the game world, including the locations of all Actors, the player, and the playing grid.
    GetOxygenTankAction
    Action that gets oxygen tank from oxygen dispenser.
    GivePlansAction
    Action that gives rocket plans to a target and get rocket body in return.
    Goon
    Class representing a Goon which is an enemy.
    Grunt
    Class representing a Grunt which is an enemy.
    InsultBehaviour
    A behaviour and also an action that has 10% chance of insulting another Actor no matter where the other Actor is.
    MoveToEarthAction
    An action that allows player to move to earth and wins the game if the player has the target boss's unconscious body in its inventory.
    Ninja
    Class representing a Ninja which is an enemy.
    OpenDoorAction
    Action that opens and go to location of a door if the actor has the correct key.
    OxygenDispenser
    Class representing an oxygen dispenser of terrain type.
    OxygenDispenserManager
    Class representing an oxygen dispenser manager.
    OxygenTank
    A class representing an oxygen tank item.
    OxygenTanks
    A thin wrapper for OxygenTank to added with oxygen tanks produced by oxygen dispenser(s).
    PressButtonAction
    An action that press the button of the oxygen dispenser to cause it to summon an oxygen dispenser manager to produce an oxygen tank in its location on the next turn.
    ProduceOxygenTankAction
    Action that produces an oxygen tank on an oxygen dispenser, then causes the actor performing this action to disappear.
    Q
    Class representing a Q.
    QuitGameAction
    Action that quits the game.
    RocketPad
    Class representing a rocket pad of terrain type.
    SafetySystem
    Class representing a safety system that keep track of player's oxygen point.
    SnapFingerAction
    An action that use gauntlet to snap finger to make all the enemies which are within 5 squares from the actor performing this action to disappear.
    SquirtAction
    An action that ha 70% of squirting water onto YugoMaxx which can destroy its exoskeleton to make it vulnerable to damage.
    StunAction
    An action and also an behaviour that throws stun powder towards the subject if subject is within 5 squares from the actor acting.
    StunnedPlayer
    Class representing a StunnedPlayer which replaces a Player when the Player is stunned.
    TalkAction
    Action that talks to the target actor accordingly depending on whether the target has rocket plans.
    UsePotionAction
    An action that uses potion to heal the hitpoint of the actor performing this action based on the heal point of the potion used.
    VisitShopAction
    Action that visits GameShop which enables Actor to buy Items using coins in coin pouch.
    Wall
    Class representing a wall of terrain type.
    WanderBehaviour
    A behaviour that allows Actor to wander around the map, allowing it to perform MoveActorAction to a random exit if there is no target beside it.
    Water
    Class representing water of water type.
    WaterPistol
    A class representing a water pistol item, it can be filled with water and it can be used to squirt water on YugoMaxx to destroy its exoskeleton.
    YugoMaxx
    Class representing a YugoMaxx which is an enemy.
